# D-FSU Mosquitto ACL.
#
# Mosquitto's `+` wildcard replaces ONE FULL topic level — you cannot mix `+`
# with literal text inside the same level. `dfsu_+_+` is rejected at parse.
# Since our device ids live inside a composite slug (`dfsu_a1b2_temperature`,
# all one level), we can't ACL-scope per-device without listing each entity.
# For local dev we trade perfect isolation for a permissive-but-readable ACL;
# tighten this before shipping publicly.

# --- Home Assistant user ---
user homeassistant
topic read  dfsu/#
topic read  homeassistant/#
topic write dfsu/+/cmd/#

# --- Per-device user. Dev only: firmware auto-derives clientId from MAC
# (e.g. `dfsu-697090`), which doesn't match a fixed slug, so the write scope
# is the whole `dfsu/#` tree. Tighten by switching to per-MAC users for prod.
user dfsu_a1b2
topic write dfsu/#
topic write homeassistant/sensor/#
topic write homeassistant/binary_sensor/#
topic write homeassistant/light/#
topic write homeassistant/select/#
topic read  dfsu/+/cmd/#
